OL,3,CRonaldsway Airport to reduce daily
OL,4,Cclosures in air traffic control ahead
OL,5,Cof TT
OL,7,FThe runway has been closed daily twice
OL,8,Fa day to allow for necessary rest
OL,9,Fbreaks, which is a regulatory
OL,10,Frequirement for those working within
OL,11,FATC.
OL,13,FCurrently the scheduled rest breaks
OL,14,Fare between 8:30-9:05am and from 11:00-
OL,15,F11:35am.
OL,17,FHowever, staff at the airport say 'a
OL,18,Fsignificant number of these closures
OL,19,Fwill no longer be necessary', due to
OL,20,F'ongoing training of air traffic
OL,21,Fcontrollers'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
